{"id":657217032,"lang":"java","time":"3Â months","timestamp":1646919723,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"3 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/657217032/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"47.5 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode() {}\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        ListNode temp= new ListNode(-1);\n        ListNode ans = temp;\n        int carry = 0;\n        while(l1!=null || l2!=null || carry !=0){\n            int sum = carry;\n            if(l1!=null){\n                sum+=l1.val;\n                l1 = l1.next;\n            }\n            if(l2!=null){\n                sum+=l2.val;\n                 l2 = l2.next;\n            }\n          //  System.out.println(sum);\n            carry = sum/10;\n            ListNode nex= new ListNode(sum%10);\n            temp.next = nex;\n            temp = temp.next;   \n          //  l1 = l1.next;\n            //l2 = l2.next;\n        }     \n        return ans.next; \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers"}
